1 persons according to the latest Federal Decennial
2 Census,
3 b. one shall be a person living in a rural community in a
4 county not situated within an urban corridor with a
5 population less than fifty thousand (50,000) persons
6 according to the latest Federal Decennial Census. For
7 purposes of this section, “urban corridor” means
8 populated areas encompassing multiples cities,
9 municipalities, or towns in clusters, often along
10 major transportation routes,
11 c. one shall be an official serving in a city, town, or
12 political subdivision in a county with a population
13 less than seventy-five thousand (75,000) persons
14 according to the latest Federal Decennial Census,
15 d. one shall represent an organization that assists
16 special populations, including, but not limited to,
17 the elderly, the disabled, veterans, and children
18 transitioning out of foster care, in obtaining
19 affordable housing, and
20 e. one shall represent an Oklahoma rural housing
21 authority;
22 2. Five members shall be appointed by the President Pro Tempore
23 of the Senate:
24
