1 a. one shall be a Senator from the majority party who
2 shall serve as co-chair of the Council,
3 b. one shall be a Senator from the minority party,
4 c. one shall represent a low-income and moderate-to-low-
5 income population-serving financial institution or a
6 community development financial institution, as
7 defined by the Federal Reserve,
8 d. one shall be an official serving in a municipality
9 with a population more than seventy-five thousand
10 (75,000) persons according to the latest Federal
11 Decennial Census, and
12 e. one shall represent an urban housing authority;
13 3. Five members shall be appointed by the Speaker of the House
14 of Representatives:
15 a. one shall be a Representative from the majority party
16 who shall serve as co-chair of the Council,
17 b. one shall be a Representative from the minority party,
18 c. one shall represent a federally recognized tribe in
19 Oklahoma that develops housing in rural areas,
20 d. one shall be a representative from a community housing
21 development organization, and
22 e. one shall represent a not-for-profit organization that
23 serves low-income Oklahomans experiencing difficulty
24 in obtaining affordable housing; and
